n \in \mathbb N
X
\mathbb R^n
(\Omega ,\mathcal F,P)
a \in \mathbb R^n
\langle X,a\rangle(\omega)=\sum_{j=1}^{n}X_{j}(\omega)a_{j}
\phi_{X}(a)=E(e^{i\langle X,a\rangle})
X=(X_{1},X_{2},\cdots,X_{n})
\{X_{i}:1\le i\le n\}
(\Omega ,\mathcal B,P)
\{X_{i}:1\le i\le n\}
\phi_{X}(a_{1},a_{2},\cdots,a_{n})=\prod_{i=1}^{n}\phi_{X_{i}}(a_{i})
a_{i}\in \mathbb R
1\le i \le n
